==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Chamois
<hw>Cham"ois</hw> <pr>(sh⟦acr⟧m"m⟦ycr⟧ <it>or</it> sh⟦adot⟧*moi";
277)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>chamois</ets>, prob. fr. OG.
<ets>gamz</ets>, G. <ets>gemse</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A small species of antelope (<spn>Rupicapra
tragus</spn>), living on the loftiest mountain ridges of Europe, as the
Alps, Pyrenees, etc. It possesses remarkable agility, and is a favorite
object of chase.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A soft leather made from the skin of the chamois, or
from sheepskin, etc.; -- called also <altname>chamois leather</altname>,
and <altname>chammy</altname> or <altname>shammy leather</altname>. See
<er>Shammy</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>chamosite</ent>⟦br⟧
